<br>
Concerning age of 8, if age of 8 is age of accountability, I suppose you let your children make their own medical decisions? After all, if they are accountable to make decision affecting the eternity of afterlife you believe in, they should be accountable to make decisions concerning this life. Do you also let them make their own decisions concerning everything else?   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#9fb7df><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/breligiousdebate60574.showUserPublicProfile?gid=rhinosmom>rhinosmom</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC="http://mjkingbird.homestead.com/files/paige.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Member</span><br>  Posts: 97<br> <font color=#3333ff>(1/8/03 8:50 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/freligiousdebate60574frm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=52.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: another question on this</span><hr size=1> Age 8 is when they start becoming more responsible, understanding, etc.<br>
