Baptism is more a religions issue, but I think what we're getting at is the underlying premise. It won't harm a child, but then neither would allowing him to choose whatever he wants to eat every day. He could choose poorly based on bad examples just as he would with religion becaue 8 is not old enough to have sense and separate onesself from ones parents and be educated enough to make an informed, mature decision. But LDS says yes they are and they are mature and smart and responsible enough to make the most important decision. If you truly believe this, you must apply the belief evenly across the board. It may be that you feel 8 year olds are old, wise and mature enough to make decisions about religion and eternity only and not movies, cars, war, marriage, sex, apartments, etc. but I doubt you'd get support for that.<br>
