<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>So my kids have some real issues to deal with and he will have an influence in thier lives. I want thier decision to be well educated and know all of the factors in mind before that decision is made.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
Having a parent out of the church makes it interesting and mixed marriages have the same problems, but you will likely have much more influence as the mother and primary care giver. If he was baptized in the Kingdom Hall and is an apostate then kudos to you for not severing contact between him and his children. I know this is more of an issue for JW than say, an ex-Catholic and his Catholic wife.<br>
